00030 \var SgClassSymbol::p_declaration
00031 \brief This pointer is always valid and stores the first non-defining declaration 
00032 where the class was defined.  
00033 
00034     It is important to note that this is the first non-defining declaration as 
00035 opposed to the defining declaration.  Thus is it the first forward declaration for the
00036 named class or a non-defining version of the declaration if the named class is
00037 defined at the locations where it was declared.
00038 
00039 \internal The value held is sharable across many references where as the defining
00040           declaration (not held by this variable) should have one unique reference
00041           within the Sage III AST, except where reference though the declarations
00042           definingDeclaration data member pointer.  See declarations for details
00043           (SgDeclarationStatements).
